Operatives of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency, NDLEA have destroyed a total of 255 hectares of cannabis farms spread across five local government areas of Ondo state.

This was made known in a press statement released today the 23rd of February, 2022, by the Agency Spokesperson, Femi Babafemi.

In an operation that lasted for 7 days, no fewer than 13 suspects were arrested and 250 kilograms of cannabis seeds as well as 63.85kg cannabis weeds were recovered in five major forests in the state.
